Traditional Leaders of South Africa aren't impressed by the attention being given to the Prince and his wife. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - Meghan Markle and four-month-old baby Archie have arrived in eGoli, while Prince Harry is in Malawi, and will return later this week. READ: Talking diversity: how accent discrimination affects SA Traditional leaders of South Africa aren't impressed by the attention being given to the Prince and his wife. READ: Traditional leaders raise concerns over attention given to British royals Greater Aboriginal Community Council of SA leader Larry Varrie said that without personally attacking the couple, they are representatives of the British monarchy who are answerable for the crimes committed in service of colonialism. "The attention should be on the issues that have never been dealt with based on colonialisation and we cannot acy as if there is nothing to be corrected in South Africa," Varrie said.